how would you feel our four year old daughter came home from home day care with make up on it was nothing major some lipstick and round lipstick circles of blush on her cheeks and pink eyeshadow i thought it was adorable her sitter explained that she was watching her put her makeup on and wanted to be a pretty big girl so she put a little on her my husband was outraged he said she doesn't need trampy makeup hes so angry he wants her out of the center i don't think its that big of a deal how would you feel i would feel fine its not like she did her make up to make her look like a year old hussy it was done in a manner that made her look like a child obviously you dont want her to wear it every day or anything but your husband is totally over reacting maybe explain to him that you understand his concern and that you will tell the sitter than you'd rather she only painted her face to look like an animal or wash it off well before sending her home my gramma used to watch us and she'd put make up on us to make us look like tigers or something so we could go play other times she'd do our make up and let us play dress up but we didnt go anywhere looking like that i dont see any harm in it at all Cosmetics Avenue Q EastEnders Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Calvin and Hobbes My Life as a Teenage Robot Kodocha The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe K' Shaggy dog story Tenchi Muyo! Humphrey Bogart Little Britain Salad Fingers Lipstick Jam (TV series) The Amber Spyglass Theory of conduct Hyuga Hinata YuYu Hakusho Texas hold 'em Social rule Sharon Tate Gender role Nine Inch Nails Marilyn Monroe Infantilism Daria About a Boy Too Short a Season (TNG episode) The Shining (film) God Emperor of Dune Teletubbies Pitaten Tris Speaker Patrick Star Characters in Bleach series Michael Garibaldi Anne Boleyn Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Beavis and Butt-head The Catcher in the Rye The Star Wars Holiday Special The Ashlee Simpson Show Firefighter Fruits Basket Faith (Buffy the V